SUMMARY:St Patty's Day Stairfinder! 🍀 (Trail Run in Forest Park)
DESCRIPTION:Northwest Trail Runners\n**Distance**: 5.7-mile mixed terrain run\n**Gain**: 800 Charming Feet\n**Start**: 1945 NW Quimby Street\n**After**: Lucky Labrador Beer Hall\n\nLet's show out on St. Patricks day🍀 with your finest green attire and flair👒. We'll start in the daylight\, heading to Lower Macleay to find some lucky trails\, then descend down the stairs back into the city and on to Lucky Lab. Don't forget your headlamps\, as the Leprechauns will not guide you in the dark 💚!\n\nThe Route:\n\n* Start at Lucky Lab\, heading west on Raleigh Street\, to NW 22nd.\n* R on NW 22nd to Thurman St.\n* L on Thurman to the stairs at the bridge.\n* Down the stairs and enter Lower Macleay Trail. Continue on past Stone House to Cornell.\n* Cross Cornell and R on Upper Macleay Trail (2.5 mi)\n* Continue on Upper Macleay\, past Wildwood Trail.\n* At 3.28 miles\, when the trail hits the neighborhood\, continue sharp left on the trail.\n* At 3.68 mi\, turn R on Cumberland Trail. Continue to Site trail and Luray Terrace (4.1 mi)\n* At mile 4.43\, turn right\, then left down the stairs. Then right on Luray Terrace.\n* At mile 4.6 Left on Cumberland\, then left down stairs\, and right on Westover.\n* Turn right down stairs then left on Summit Ave.\n* Turn right on Cornell\, then left on Stairs.\n* Continue on Overton Ave to NW 20th St. Turn Left.\n* Continue on NW 20th to NW Quimby and finish.\n\nhttps://www.strava.com/routes/3466841718972247244\nhttps://onthegomap.com/?route=019cddea-7abc-7f30-a186-8333df37c24f&context=share\n\nAfterwards we'll celebrate our green attire\, Irish beer\, and longer days at The Lucky Labrador Beer Hall!\n\nSee you there!\nHosted by: Dionne\nNorthwest Trail Runners
